solidbase.core.plugins
Class ImportCSV

java.lang.Object
  solidbase.core.CommandListener
      solidbase.core.plugins.ImportCSV

public class ImportCSV
extends CommandListener

This plugin executes IMPORT CSV statements. 

 IMPORT CSV INTO tablename
 "xxxx1","yyyy1","zzzz1"
 "xxxx2","yyyy2","zzzz2"
 GO

Since:
Dec 2, 2009
Author:
René M. de Bloois

Description copied from class: CommandListener
Called when a command from the upgrade file needs to be executed. Commands can be transient or persistent (see Command.isTransient). This method should return true if it decides to process the command.

Specified by:
execute in class CommandListener

Import data using a PL/SQL BEGIN/END block, like this: 
 BEGIN
     INSERT INTO TABLE1 VALUES ( VALUE1, VALUE2 );
     INSERT INTO TABLE1 VALUES ( VALUE1, VALUE2 );
     INSERT INTO TABLE1 VALUES ( VALUE1, VALUE2 );
 END;

Parameters:
command - The import command.
connection - The connection with the database.
reader - The CSV reader.
parsed - The parsed command.
line - The first line of data read.
Throws:
SQLException - Whenever SQL execution throws it.
IOException - Whenever CSV reading throws it.
